docs.snippet: The luxury brand wants Hong Kong shops to stop selling cardboard replicas of its shoes, bags and other products to be burned as offerings to the dead....
docs.lead_paragraph: The luxury brand wants Hong Kong shops to stop selling cardboard replicas of its shoes, bags and other products to be burned as offerings to the dead.
docs.abstract: Hong Kong Journal; decision by Kering, Gucci's Paris-based parent company, to make stand only in Hong Kong against sale of paper replicas of Gucci products points to city's growing status in world; replicas, which are burnt as offerings to deceased, have also cropped up in New York, Beijing, Bangkok and other cities.

headline.main: Rest in Peace ... Just Not in Gucci Loafers
headline.print_headline: May They Rest in Peace ... but Please, Not in Gucci Loafers
